questions.text:
What is the output of the following code?

```java
int x = 0;
if (x < 4) {
  x = x + 1;
}
System.out.println("x is " + x);
```

Suppose `income` is 4001, what is the output of the following code?

```java
if (income > 3000) {
  System.out.println("Income is greater than 3000");
}
else if (income > 4000) {
  System.out.println("Income is greater than 4000");
}
```

The following code displays __________.

```java
double temperature = 50;

if (temperature >= 100)
  System.out.println("too hot");
else if (temperature <= 40)
  System.out.println("too cold");
else
  System.out.println("just right");
```

Suppose `x = 1`, `y = -1`, and `z = 1`. What is the output of the following statement? (Hint: Consider the 'dangling else' rule and proper indentation.)

```java
if (x > 0)
  if (y > 0)
    System.out.println("x > 0 and y > 0");
  else if (z > 0)
    System.out.println("x < 0 and z > 0");
```

Analyze the following code:

```java
boolean even = false;
if (even = true) {
  System.out.println("It is even");
}
```

Analyze the following code:

```java
boolean even = false;
if (even) {
  System.out.println("It is even!");
}
```

Analyze the following code:

**Code 1:**
```java
int number = 45;
boolean even;

if (number % 2 == 0) 
  even = true;
else 
  even = false;
```

**Code 2:**
```java
int number = 45;
boolean even = (number % 2 == 0);
```

Suppose you write the code to display "Cannot get a driver's license" if `age` is less than 16 and "Can get a driver's license" if `age` is greater than or equal to 16. Which of the following code snippets is correct? Please select all that apply.

**I:**
```java
